Here are pilot participants comments on the experiment:

userid comments problems
abdellah na no
dmp im an experimenter
Domormsby Not that I noticed
gaylene.gondolfi the questions at the beginning were fun. when they started asking for numbers, I wanted to use words - which was not acceptable. it then became frustrating. I felt it was then a waste of everyones time because I was only guessing. but, I was also just trying to guess for myself, what is this HIT really trying to test? :) Im guessing it was whether I thought I read the instructions correctly? it was silly to ask how many. only a study can answer that and there are so many variables so, of course my answers are not correct
hfbennett It is interesting. no
kara i dont know enough about malaria to answer the questions well, so i felt a little dumb doing it. i also felt like i was being evaluated on the (in)consistencies in my statistical reasoning - that was very transparent and a little uncomfortable. i also happened to choose a disease that tends to affect a wide range of people with radically different access to a cure, so i felt dumb answering how hard it would be to get medicine. so basically, i felt dumb. but it was very easy to do!
samilizzy What does HIT stand for? I dont know if I did this experiment right. Was I just supposed to make up a random illness? Thats what I did. It was kind of fun to get asked questions related to my answers by a computer. No, I dont think so. All the questions made sense grammatically.
unkown_user i am in love with the experimenter smokes was used incorrectly somehow
weiner nothing serious that i noticed

In general, enough people felt silly or dumb while filling this out that I think we need to improve the interface or the cover story a bit. People are worried about getting stuff wrong. What are some ways of framing this so that they feel comfortable with guessing?
